reviews.text: This was me and my husband first time here, and they were absolutely slammed.   Despite how busy they were, they still got my husband and I seated fairly quickly.  Our waiter was attentive, and we didn't have to wait long at all for our food (which was delicious!).  The live music was awesome!  They are a little bit on the pricey side but well worth it.

The atmosphere was great, warm and fun. The food was really worth the nice wait (We liked the pace). Great ribs, the shrimp with Macaroni was superb (a light creamy sauce on the ziti pasta, with 8 jumbo shrimp on top seasoned beautifully), great roasted red potatoes as veg, and sauteed veggies too. The price was more than fair for a good meal. Thanks, Brickyard. We'll be back.
This a great place for a cozy dinner with your "significant other"!  Food, service and atmosphere are incredible!  The City center is also very nice to visit.
The Atmosphere is very homey and the food is delicious. If I lived in Kentucky this would be one of my hangouts. Going back home to San Diego, Ca. this Sunday but I will be back for the Derby.❤

Craving lasagna?  Then this is the place to come! Excellent balance of meats, cheeses, and spices... and the sauce tastes garden-fresh!
Pair it with a side salad, and the appetizer bread and you've got a deliciously filling meal!
Great bbq! Huge portions! Its all great!❗Nice people ❗U gotta try it❗

When they are open, go there. You won't find better BBQ in the state (following the closing of Staten's BBQ in 2013), and you'll struggle to find a better BBQ joint in Tennessee too. Locals know Dunn has the best BBQ, but travelers may see a grey brick building with no parking and decide to go elsewhere. This would be a mistake. I'd park in front of a fire hydrant in between a cop and a tow truck and walk 2 blocks just to get some of those ribs!

I honestly wasn't sure if this was an actual restaurant when I first saw the building, boy I'm glad I went in though. It's handmade, home smoked and deliciously tender barbeque. With some of the sweetest Coleslaw I've ever tasted made it an excellent lunch option. They tend to run out in the few hours a week they're open so get there early and enjoy.
Dunn's is a hidden gem. Best BBQ and the friendliest person you'll ever meet.
Excellent food. Never disappoints!
Great burgers, fries, shakes and more. But my favorite is their Brown Derby, a vanilla ice cream cone dipped in chocolate. The best!

This little gem has the best sliders! Forget Krystal and forget White Castle these little babies are super fresh, have a fantastic melt in your mouth flavor and do not leave you with the after taste of their competition. Highly recommended spot for a tasty snack.
The food was good but i got the small burger and ended up being the sise of a Cristal and the milkshake was kinda thick
Love the Frosty Freeze. Great place for old fashioned burgers, sandwiches, fries, ice cream and shakes!!
Great little old school place for a burger and a dipped cone. Been stopping by for about 55 years now.
New owner????
Such a great place! Nice staff, good food, fast service. Highly recommend.
Excellent place to wine an dine an listen to live music an the food is terrific been here several times an never had a bad experience
Service was fantastic And the food was delicious.the price was very reasonable.

Ordered take out through the app. Our food was screwed up AND they left out the extra chips and salsa we ordered. When we called up there, instead of apologizing, they instantly became super defensive and just argued. No offer to fix the issue or any type of care that it was screwed up. Won't be back. Very unprofessional.

Great barbecue and great sides. I almost always get the brisket, coleslaw, and the hog fries (seasoned fries). This place is very popular for lunch and can get busy, but I have always gotten my food pretty quickly. They have several different BBQ sauces out and I really enjoy their spice BBQ sauce. The price is very reasonable and portions are good. I highly recommend this restaurant.

I just love this place! You can smell the BBQ when you open the door. The food is the best BBQ you will find around. And we are always greeted with smiling faces waiting to help us. Thank you Wildfire for making so many wonderful dinning experiences!

Was in town for work and ate here several times during the week. GREAT food and great atmosphere. The owner was very nice and the rest of the staff was great as well. Highly recommend if you're anywhere near the area.
Delicious smoked meats with a variety of BBQ sauces to choose from. Spicy, tangy or sweet and smokey is my favorite. Mild sauce or spicy medium or hot spicy. Great choice of sides. Great folks.

Hidden BBQ treasure just off I-65 in small town Kentucky.  Small Pit BBQ place that feels homey and tastes amazing.  Everything from the pork to the cornbread and sides was scrumptious and memorable and even my picky toddler couldn't resist trying some.  Exactly the kind of BBQ place I love to find and you should definitely try it.
